title: An incumbent governor defeats a former one as Mills bests LePage in Maine.
description: Gov. Janet Mills of Maine, a Democrat, campaigned on preserving abortion access. She beat former Gov. Paul LePage, a Republican who sought a nonconsecutive third term.
dc:creator: Alyce McFadden

media:content.media:description: Gov. Janet Mills of Maine, the incumbent and a Democrat, at a rally in York this month. She campaigned on preserving abortion access.
